// Auto-layout computation
// Drives Yoga-based flexbox layout for SceneGraph frames, translating node sizing/alignment properties into a Yoga tree, running layout, and writing computed positions and sizes back to the graph.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

FUNCTION computeLayout(graph: SceneGraph, frameId: string) -> void [2026-03-26] EXPORT
  CALLS: getNode, getChildren, updateNode (scene-graph)
  Builds a Yoga node tree for a single frame, runs calculateLayout, applies the results back to the graph via applyYogaLayout, then frees the tree.

---

FUNCTION computeAllLayouts(graph: SceneGraph) -> void [2026-03-26]      EXPORT
  CALLS: computeLayout (layout)
  Traverses the entire scene graph bottom-up and calls computeLayout on every frame whose layoutMode is not NONE, ensuring children are laid out before parents.

---

FUNCTION buildYogaTree(graph, frame) -> YogaNode [2026-03-26]
  Creates the root Yoga node from a frame's sizing, direction, wrap, justify, align, padding, and gap properties. Recursively creates child nodes via configureChildAsAutoLayout or configureChildAsLeaf, skipping absolutely-positioned children.

---

FUNCTION configureChildAsAutoLayout(yogaChild, child, parent, graph) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Configures a Yoga child node that is itself an auto-layout frame: sets flex direction, wrap, justify, align, padding, gap, and sizing based on the child's own layout properties and its relationship to the parent axis. Recurses into grandchildren.

---

FUNCTION configureChildAsLeaf(yogaChild, child, parent) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Configures a Yoga child node for a non-frame leaf element: sets fixed width/height or flex-grow based on layoutGrow, and applies stretch alignment if needed.

---

FUNCTION setSizing(yogaNode, axis, sizing, fixedValue, grow) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Applies FIXED (setWidth/setHeight), HUG (no-op, natural size), or FILL (flex-grow) sizing to a Yoga node axis. If grow > 0, flex-grow takes precedence.

---

FUNCTION applyYogaLayout(graph, frame, yogaNode) -> void [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: updateNode, getChildren (scene-graph)
  Reads computed positions and sizes from Yoga nodes and writes them back to the graph. If the frame uses HUG sizing, also updates the frame's own width/height. Recurses into auto-layout children.

---

FUNCTION freeYogaTree(node: YogaNode) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Recursively frees all Yoga nodes in the tree to avoid memory leaks in the WASM heap.
